recordings.file-name: Harpactes_oreskios_stellaei-FL song (2 birds) Seima Cambodia 20Apr12 150m LS110297.mp3
recordings.rmk: Two birds (at least one male - the closest bird) on this cut. The song here seems unusually long, comprising 8-9 notes and on one phrase 11 notes - more usually there are only 3-6 notes. Perhaps the increased number of notes relates to the presence of a second bird and some kind of territorial dispute is taking place.

recordings.file-name: XC145302-AUD_0295 Luntur harimau (Harpactes oreskios) Orange-breasted Trogon Jogging track-Cangar.mp3
recordings.rmk: The forest is quite pristine with dense canopy; the weather was sunny; lots of Kukrup trees (Engelhardia spicata) and Pasang trees. Distance from observer is approx. 10 m,

Although low quality I thought it worth uploading this as a site record and because this subspecies seems to have a longer call than those on mainland SE Asia, with 7-9 notes, and seems to be delivered slightly faster than its mainland counterparts. Two cuts spliced together of the same individual
